parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbags to not deploy in the event of an accident, leading to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The "Check Airbag System" warning light comes on intermittently
sometimes staying on for a few days or weeks
and then turning off. The light may come on when the vehicle is started
or while driving. In some cases
the passenger airbag warning light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unexpected deployment of airbags can cause injury or distraction, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Airbags deploy without any apparent impact or collision

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Airbags to Deploy in Accident
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in an accident can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in an accident
despite the vehicle being involved in a collision.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the VSA modulator can cause the loss of vehicle stability and traction, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: and VSA lights illuminate on the dashboard
and the vehicle may experience a loss of power steering

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electric power steering can cause the loss of power steering, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, and increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The power steering light illuminates on the dashboard
and the vehicle may experience a loss of power steering
making it difficult to turn the steering wheel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS and brake system can cause the loss of braking functionality, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The ABS and brake system lights illuminate on the dashboard
and the vehicle may experience a loss of braking functionality.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the VSA module can cause the ABS system to malfunction, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
The failure of the airbag system can lead to failure to deploy in the event of an accident, resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Airbag warning light on the dashboard
failure to deploy in an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a range of problems, including loss of power, stalling, and failure of critical systems like the airbag system.
Rodent damage to wiring can cause a range of problems, including electrical system failure, loss of power, and stalling.
The failure of the horn can increase the risk of accidents, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's presence.
The failure of the infotainment system can cause distraction and increase the risk of accidents.
